            <p class="pt-md-4">This Instructor Agreement (“<span class="font-dubai-bold">Agreement</span>”) is entered into by amongst <span class="font-dubai-bold">LYVYO LLC</span> incorporated in United Arab Emirates (hereinafter referred to as “<span>LYVYO</span>”, which expression shall unless it be repugnant to the context or meaning thereof, be deemed to mean and include its affiliates, administrators, liquidators, successors and permitted assigns) and the Instructor.</p>
            <h5 class="py-md-3 font-dubai-bold">WHEREAS</h5>
            <p class="">1. LYVYO is engaged in the business of providing online educational, fitness services and consultancy services, including but not limited to providing guidance and mentorship services to the Learner.</p>
            <p class="py-md-1">2. The Instructor is providing to the Learners generic information of services that are provided on LYVYO.</p>
            <p class="py-md-1">3. The Parties are desirous to enter into this Instructor Agreement in consideration of the mutual promises, covenants, undertakings and agreements between the Parties hereto, and on the terms and conditions contained herein.</p>
            <p class="py-md-1"><span>1. NOW THEREFORE</span>, in consideration of the foregoing and other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and adequacy of which are hereby expressly acknowledged, the Parties, intending to be legally bound, hereby agree as follows:</p>

            <h5 class="font-dubai-bold pt-md-2 ">1. DEFINITIONS</h5>

            <p class="">The Instructor hereby unconditionally agrees that unless the context otherwise requires, the definitions listed below when used in this Agreement shall have the meanings attached to them and these terms shall be interpreted accordingly. The definitions listed below as used in this Agreement may be identified by the capitalization of the first letter of each principal word thereof. In addition to the terms defined below, certain other capitalized terms are defined elsewhere in this Agreement and whenever such terms are used in this Agreement, they shall have their respective defined meanings, unless the context, expressly or by necessary implication, require otherwise:</p>

            <p class="py-md-2">1. “Applicable Law” includes all applicable statutes, enactments, acts of state legislatures or parliament, laws, ordinances, rules, bye-laws, regulations, notifications, Instructor lines, policies, directions, directives and orders of any Government, statutory authority, tribunal, board, court or any other relevant jurisdiction.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">2. “Confidential Information” means any and all of the Company business plans, mechanisms, business related functions, activities and services, customer lists, knowledge of customer  needs  and preferences, trade secrets,  business  strategies, marketing strategies, methods of operation, tax records, markets, other valuable information, confidential information and trade related information relating to the business and activities of the Company and useful or necessary for the success of the Company’s business and activities. Confidential  Information  shall also include financial  information,  such  as the Company’s earnings, assets,  debts,  prices,  pricing structure,  estimates,  volumes  of customers,  transaction  details  such  as names  or address, terms of services, contracts of particular transactions, or related information about the Company employees, customers, potential customers; marketing information, such as details about ongoing or proposed marketing programs or agreements by or on behalf of  the Company, projections, sales forecasts or results of marketing efforts or information about impending transactions; personnel information; and customer information, such as any compilation of past, existing  or prospective  customers, customers’ proposals  or agreements  between  customers  and status  of customers’ accounts or credit, or related information about actual or prospective customers.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">3. “Liquidation Event” shall mean (I) voluntary or involuntary liquidation, dissolution or winding up of LYVYO, a merger, acquisition, change of control, consolidation, or other transaction or series of transactions in which the Shareholders prior to such transaction will not: (a) retain a majority of the voting power of the surviving entity, or (b) control the board of directors of the surviving entity, or (ii) a sale, lease, license or other transfer of all or substantially all the LYVYO’s assets or (iii) ceasing of operations of LYVYO within a particular country and/or geographic location(s).</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">4. “Learner” shall mean the Learner of the online services / classes provided by LYVYO, as a means of counselling, Fitness and Education including but not limited to the activities envisaged under this Agreement.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">5. “Indemnified Liabilities” shall have the meaning ascribed to it in Clause 8.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">6. “Indemnified Parties” shall have the meaning ascribed to it in Clause 8.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">7. “Services” shall mean any and all services, whether through online and offline medium provided either directly and/or indirectly by LYVYO. </p>

            <p class="py-md-1">8. “Session” shall mean the session between the Learner and the Instructor.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">9. “Instructor Consideration” shall have the meaning ascribed to it in Clause 4.</p>


            <h5 class="font-dubai-bold pt-md-2  ">2. GENERAL INTERPRETATION</h5>
            <p class="">In this Agreement, except to the extent that the context otherwise requires:</p>
            <p class="">1. References to a statute, ordinance or other Law shall be deemed to include any references to a statute, ordinance or other Law as amended, supplemented or replaced from time to time in accordance with its terms and (where applicable) subject to compliance with the requirements set forth therein and shall include regulations and other instruments under such statue, ordinance or other Law;</p>

            <p class="py-md-2">2. References to Clauses, Annexures and Schedules are reference to clauses in and annexures and schedules to this Agreement unless the context requires otherwise and the Annexures and Schedules to this Agreement shall always be deemed to form part of this Agreement;
            </p>

            <p class="">3. The headings are inserted for convenience only and shall not affect the construction of this Agreement;</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">4. The Masculine includes the Feminine Gender e.g., a ‘he’ should also be read as ‘she’, and vice versa.</p>


            <h5 class="font-dubai-bold pt-md-2 ">2. DUTIES OF INSTRUCTOR</h5>
            <p class="">1. The Instructor shall provide the Learner information in relation to his relevant and specific educational and degrees/subjects along with any other necessary information, in consonance with acceptable industry practices. The insights provided has to be factual and based on the Instructor’s own experiences only.</p>

            <p class="py-md-2">2. The Instructor acknowledges, affirms, agrees and understands that the services provided to the Learner may vary on a case-to-case basis on an individual basis based on the respective queries of the Learner.
            </p>

            <p class="">3. The Instructor has the specific knowledge of the educational subjects and degree course/subjects and other relevant services they sign up to provide.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">4. Notwithstanding anything contained herein, the Instructor shall adhere to any and all regulatory compliances and specifications as may be required under Applicable Law, including but not limited to disclosure certificate from the Disclosure and Barring Service (England and Wales), Protecting Vulnerable Groups (PVG) scheme (Scotland), Children’s Online Privacy Protection Rule (United States of America) and/or Accessing.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">5. The Instructor affirms, acknowledges, agrees and understands that any content shared by him to the Learner shall be considered non-confidential, to the extent permitted by law.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">6. The Instructor acknowledges, agrees, affirms and understands that directly and/or indirectly, for sharing of nudity, pornographic or adult material, sexually explicit images or descriptions involving sexual behavior, or other content deemed offensive by LYVYO according to community standards and/or Applicable Law, is strictly prohibited.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">7. The Instructor acknowledges, affirms, agrees and understands that he shall have no claim or other recourse (and/or otherwise disclaims) against LYVYO for infringement of any proprietary right in relation to any matter envisaged under this Agreement.
            </p>

            <p class="py-md-1">8. The Instructor acknowledges, affirms, agrees and understands that all services envisaged under this Agreement has been provided at the Instructor’s own risk.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">9. LYVYO cannot and does not guarantee that the Sessions shall not be viewed by unauthorized persons.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">10. The Instructor shall not make any misrepresentations and/or provide false information with regards to LYVYO and/or any third party during the sessions or about their own experiences of the educational institution(s), degree course(s)/subjects that he will provide information on and per the Instructor’s profile on LYVYO’s website and platform.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">11. At the instance, an Instructor is unavailable for any Session, for any reason whatsoever, he shall not have entitled to the Instructor Consideration in relation to such Session. In case the Session was prepaid, LYVYO shall be entitled to a full refund, along with interest. The rights of LYVYO under this Clause shall be cumulative and not in alternate with the other rights that are vested at such an instance (including but not limited to damages and indemnification).
            </p>

            <p class="py-md-1">12. The Instructor shall only use Standard English with the Learner unless otherwise instructed by LYVYO or at the request of the Learner based on the spoken languages listed by the Instructor on LYVYO’s platform.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">13. In case of emergency rescheduling a valid reason for such rescheduling shall be corroborated with proper documentation which shall be allowed at the discretion of LYVYO and as such if rejected the Instructor shall be bound to refund such considerations allotted to him and/or (at the option of LYVYO) shall make available such Services that were denied to such Learner in lieu of such rescheduling at any time which the Learner may deem fit.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">14. The Instructor shall always maintain a positive attitude throughout any Session and never show signs of frustration or anger.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">15. During any Session, the Instructor shall at all times dress professionally and in an appropriate manner.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">16. The Instructor shall keep LYVYO informed of any issues or problems with a Learner, as and when they develop.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">17. The Instructor shall under no circumstances discuss or share any personal information, contact information or social media with the Learner nor shall he entertain such discussions on the part of the Learner.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">18. The Instructor shall bear all local taxes as he or she may be subject to in his/ her country.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">19. The Instructor shall not engage in any activity and/or conversation with the Learner other than strictly for the purposes specifically laid down under these Agreement, prior to, during the continuance of, and after each and every Session.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">20. The Instructor undertakes to promptly notify LYVYO at the instance the Learner engages into any activity, conversation and/or conduct which falls outside the purview of this Agreement prior to, during the continuance of, and after any Session.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">21. The Instructor specifically represents and warrants that he shall not initiate and/or continue any (personal, professional and/or otherwise) relationship with the Learner in any manner whatsoever.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">22. The Instructor shall not make any disparaging statements in relation to any person and/or organization during his interaction with the Learner, whether during a Session or afterwards, including but not limited to the educational institution(s) he has been a part of and any of its professors, teachers, instructors and members in the administration and support staff. Instructor must always remain professional, unbiased and only share factual information and insights based on his own experiences only. For clarification of doubt, the Instructor specifically represents and warrants that all information that is provided is true and accurate.</p>


            <h5 class="font-dubai-bold pt-md-2 ">3. RIGHTS OF LYVYO</h5>
            <p class="">1. LYVYO shall have the sole right to receive payments from any person in relation to the Services and any part thereof. For clarification of doubt, it is hereby stated that under no circumstances shall the Instructor derive any monetary benefit, whether directly or indirectly, in the form of monies and/or otherwise, from any client of LYVYO.</p>

            <p class="py-md-2">2. LYVYO reserves the right to enquire, cross check and/or otherwise validate the authenticity of the Educational Qualification in any manner that LYVYO deems fit (including requesting the Instructor to have the educational institution(s) send an attested degree certificate and other documents directly to LYVYO in a sealed envelope. LYVYO reserves the right to use technology to authenticate the genuineness of the degree certificates and any other documents provided by the Instructor on LYVYO platform. LYVYO reserves the right to freeze or delete the Instructor profile if the documents are not provided within a timeframe acceptable to LYVYO.
            </p>

            <p class="">3. LYVYO reserves the right to enter into independent Instructor agreements with third parties, in relation to the same subject matter as envisaged under this Agreement. For avoidance of doubt, it is hereby clarified that this Agreement does not give the Instructor any exclusive rights in relation to activities envisaged herein.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">4. Subject to Applicable Law, LYVYO reserves the right to use any and all information that has been provided by the Instructor, whether in non-aggregated form or otherwise, for any marketing and/or promotional purposes (including videos, photos etc.).</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">5. Nothing in this Agreement shall restrict LYVYO from expanding to other commercial markets in any manner whatsoever, including but not limited to in collaboration with other third-party partners and/or Instructors.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">6. Notwithstanding anything contained herein, LYVYO shall have a unilateral right to terminate this Agreement.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">7. Subject to Applicable Law, LYVYO reserves the right to ask for more information from the Instructor which is directly connected to the Services.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">8. LYVYO reserves its right to monitor and/or record the use of all or any part of any Session.</p>


            <h5 class="font-dubai-bold pt-md-2 ">4. PAYMENTS</h5>
            <p class="">1. LYVYO will allow instructors to place their own pricing structures in line with market practice and geographical locations. This will include a fixed fee for private sessions and a fixed fee for group sessions. (“Instructor Consideration”). The terms of the payment structure envisaged herein shall be read in consonance with the structure delineated in the LYVYO’s website. For clarification of doubt, at times of the conflict, the terms of this Agreement shall supersede the terms laid down on LYVYO’s website. LYVYO shall be entitled to deduct a commission of amounts from every transaction occurring in its platform. </p>

            <p class="py-md-2">2. At the instance of any promotional discount provided by LYVYO to any and all End Customer’s up to the extent of 25% of the Instructor Consideration, the Instructor specifically agrees to such reduction to his remuneration and specifically disclaims any and all rights pursuant thereto under any contract, applicable law and/or equity. Promotional discounts will be conveyed to the Instructor beforehand. Remaining balance of promotional discounts provided to Learners will be reimbursed back to Instructors by LYVYO. </p>

            <p class="">3. Commission collected by LYVYO will be at a fixed rate of 20 %. First a 10% commission will be deducted once the Learner pays LYVYO. A Second 10% is deducted from that amount and then sent to the instructor. LYVYO has the power to change these commission rates at any given time. Instructors will be informed prior to any changes. Commissions will not be deducted on the VAT amount added on the invoice of each payment. </p>

            <p class="py-md-1">4. Notwithstanding anything contained herein, the Instructor understands, agrees, affirms and acknowledges that the Instructor Remuneration shall be the full and complete remuneration for any and all services envisaged under this Agreement.</p>

            <p class="py-md-1">5. LYVYO reserves the right to amend the payment amount or structure in any transaction that falls within the purview of this Agreement from time to time for any reason whatsoever, subject to due notification of such amendment to the Instructor (either via electronic means or a broadcast on LYVYO’s website) and the Instructor specifically disclaims any and all rights that vest upon him under any contract, law or equity in this regard </p>


            <h5 class="font-dubai-bold pt-md-2 ">5. EFFECTIVE DATE</h5>
            <p class="">The Effective Date of this Agreement shall be the date on which the Instructor accepts these terms on LYVYO platform in accordance with the process of registration and approval of the Instructor by LYVYO.</p>


            <h5 class="font-dubai-bold pt-md-2 ">6. DECLARATIONS, REPRESENTATIONS, WARRANTIES AND COVENANTS</h5>
            <p class="">1. Each Party hereby warrants that he has the legal right, power and authority to enter into, deliver and perform this Agreement and any other documents executed by him in connection with or pursuant thereto. </p>

